#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Pre-commit hook: refuse commits with ocamlformat-visible defects.
#
# Activated by symlink via tools/git-hooks/install.sh. The hook lives
# under tools/ (tracked) rather than .git/hooks/ (untracked) so updates
# propagate to every developer who runs the installer.
#
# Two gating conditions on the [dune build @fmt] output:
#
#   1. Format drift — any line matching [^--- ] in the formatter
#      output indicates an actual diff between source and the
#      formatted version. Always reject.
#
#   2. Format blind spots — any line matching [Warning 50] or
#      [ocamlformat: ignoring]. ocamlformat skips files whose
#      shape it can't process (most commonly a [(** ... *)]
#      docstring the parser can't bind to). A skipped file is a
#      hole in our format coverage; the offending construct must
#      be removed before commit.
#
# Why not gate at the OCaml compiler with [-w @50]: any file
# preprocessed by ppx (e.g. [@@deriving yojson]) has its
# docstrings stripped before reaching the compiler, so a
# compiler-level warning never fires for the docstring in the
# original source. ocamlformat works from its own parser without
# ppx interposition, and is the only stage that reliably sees
# the source as-written.

set -e

staged_ocaml=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACM 2>/dev/null \
               | grep -E '\.(ml|mli)$' || true)
if [ -z "$staged_ocaml" ]; then
  exit 0
fi

# Capture both stdout and stderr. The exit code mixes drift,
# warnings, and "ignored file" notes; we discriminate by grepping
# the output for the precise signals we care about.
fmt_output=$(opam exec -- dune build @fmt 2>&1) || true

if echo "$fmt_output" | grep -qE '^--- '; then
  cat >&2 <<'MSG'

ocamlformat drift detected.

To apply the formatter and re-stage:

    opam exec -- dune build @fmt --auto-promote
    git add -u
    git commit  # re-run

The hook checks the full project, not only staged files, because
ocamlformat config changes can render previously-compliant files
non-compliant; catching the full set here keeps drift from
accumulating between explicit fmt sweeps.

MSG
  exit 1
fi

if echo "$fmt_output" | grep -qE 'Warning 50|ocamlformat: ignoring'; then
  cat >&2 <<'MSG'

ocamlformat refused to process at least one file.

This is most often a misplaced [(** ... *)] docstring — a
documentation comment sitting in a position the parser can't
bind to an item (e.g. between two [let X = ... in] inside a
let-chain). odoc can't render it, and ocamlformat skips the
entire file, leaving it invisible to the format gate.

Fix: relocate the docstring to attach to a top-level item,
or downgrade to a regular [(* ... *)] comment if it doesn't
need odoc rendering.

The offending file(s) and lines:

MSG
  echo "$fmt_output" | grep -E 'ignoring|Warning 50|^File ' | head -30 >&2
  exit 1
fi
